'Every time I would walk to the bus, you know, I would make up these little fibs to kids that I was in school with that, "oh no, I don't live there. I live in a nice house across the street,''' Scheidt, now 21, told ABC News' "20/20" in an episode that will air tonight at 10 p.m.

Scheidt said that he always had a love of medicine and that he would read about health and watch doctor television shows such as Grey's Anatomy and E.R. He also had an app on his phone that would teach him about the human anatomy.

