Scheidt's premature involvement in medicine began when he wasn't yet a teenager.

When Schiedt was just 11-years-old he volunteered at a Florida hospital and lied about his age because the minimum age for volunteers was 14-years-old.

When Scheidt was only 13-years-old he was caught pretending to be a nurse at a Florida hospital but no charges were made against him.

